    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that \"debunked\" stuff always feels like a convenient way to shut down any real inquiry. if it was just minor errors, why are so many of the original telemetry tapes actually missing? it's a huge coincidence that the most critical data from the supposed \"discovery\" era is what disappeared. if i want to look for patterns in what's NOT there—like gaps in the mission logs or weirdly timed redactions—can u help me figure out where those holes usually are?",
